 <sect1 id="release-17-1">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=c2963ca4d7e670cbba117a86653e5b1c sig_cn_org=dcd47c19b688eee2471b898f4e151c9f source=17.5 
  <title>Release 17.1</title>
________________________________________________________-->
  <title>版本 17.1</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=c2963ca4d7e670cbba117a86653e5b1c -->

  <formalpara>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=c45e8127eac45f2347bf1713afaeffda sig_cn_org=253305b4c6dff5b87ef36e3c2d95e52e source=15.7 
  <title>Release date:</title>
________________________________________________________-->
  <title>发布日期：</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=c45e8127eac45f2347bf1713afaeffda -->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=c3f5709eb4f0214271fc9dfa4c103cb3 sig_cn_org=c3f5709eb4f0214271fc9dfa4c103cb3 source=16.8 
  <para>2024-11-14</para>
________________________________________________________-->
  <para>2024-11-14</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=c3f5709eb4f0214271fc9dfa4c103cb3 -->
  </formalpara>

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=64f782c92162997f1789b055c218ce6e sig_cn_org=8cce625043a2d02c37417776bd8d62f9 source=17.5 
  <para>
   This release contains a variety of fixes from 17.0.
   For information about new features in major release 17, see
   <xref linkend="release-17"/>.
  </para>
________________________________________________________-->
  <para>
   本版本包含了来自17.0的各种修复。
   有关17大版本中新功能的信息，请参见
   <xref linkend="release-17"/>.
  </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=64f782c92162997f1789b055c218ce6e -->

  <sect2 id="release-17-1-migration">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=51d56959b5846e5d6c6942d1884e02af sig_cn_org=afc6f34a3a41d0fa6621af12d29fc61a source=17.5 
   <title>Migration to Version 17.1</title>
________________________________________________________-->
   <title>迁移到版本 17.1</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=51d56959b5846e5d6c6942d1884e02af -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=e5363a119f0af3092f384dea35785515 sig_cn_org=012eec4b41a96b7ba9e089d7d12eee97 source=17.5 
   <para>
    A dump/restore is not required for those running 17.X.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    对于运行17.X的用户，不需要进行转储/恢复操作。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=e5363a119f0af3092f384dea35785515 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=1fb2d416f6883355a960fdfcc630e501 sig_cn_org=8f9f91cd06dfcb68d46c3f393240b0c5 source=16.8 
   <para>
    However, if you have ever detached a partition from a partitioned
    table that has a foreign-key reference to another partitioned table,
    and not dropped the former partition, then you may have catalog and/or
    data corruption to repair, as detailed in the fifth changelog entry
    below.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    然而，如果您曾经从一个分区表中分离出一个分区，并且该分区表具有对另一个
    分区表的外键引用，而没有删除前者的分区，那么您可能需要修复目录和/或数据
    损坏，具体细节请参见下面的第五个变更日志条目。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=1fb2d416f6883355a960fdfcc630e501 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=6258639bb728edd1593e9f2af6248dee sig_cn_org=d3d6d05350aba67fb918ae274bb77f4f source=17.5 
   <para>
    Also, in the uncommon case that a
    database's <varname>LC_CTYPE</varname> setting is <literal>C</literal>
    while its <varname>LC_COLLATE</varname> setting is some other locale,
    indexes on textual columns should be reindexed, as described in the
    sixth changelog entry below.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    另外，在不常见的情况下，如果数据库的<varname>LC_CTYPE</varname>设置为<literal>C</literal>，
    而其<varname>LC_COLLATE</varname>设置为其他区域设置，则应重新索引文本列上的索引，
    如下面第六条变更日志条目中所述。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=6258639bb728edd1593e9f2af6248dee -->
  </sect2>

  <sect2 id="release-17-1-changes">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=e161fef38e54e54458e215e5f978ef9b sig_cn_org=f104d50dd9d4dd802f94229ebe5bc097 source=15.7 
   <title>Changes</title>
________________________________________________________-->
   <title>变更</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=e161fef38e54e54458e215e5f978ef9b -->

   <itemizedlist>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Nathan Bossart <nathan@postgresql.org>
Branch: master [cd7ab5753] 2024-11-11 09:00:00 -0600
Branch: REL_17_STABLE [edcda9bb4] 2024-11-11 09:00:00 -0600
Branch: REL_16_STABLE [562289460] 2024-11-11 09:00:00 -0600
Branch: REL_15_STABLE [6db5ea8de] 2024-11-11 09:00:00 -0600
Branch: REL_14_STABLE [4e51030af] 2024-11-11 09:00:00 -0600
Branch: REL_13_STABLE [952ff31e2] 2024-11-11 09:00:00 -0600
Branch: REL_12_STABLE [448525e8a] 2024-11-11 09:00:00 -0600
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=57b9d20188f7df33008b88594e942983 sig_cn_org=3eb921c5a178cea315ae225fef7a7117 source=17.5 
     <para>
      Ensure cached plans are marked as dependent on the calling role when
      RLS applies to a non-top-level table reference (Nathan Bossart)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;edcda9bb4">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      确保当行级安全（RLS）应用于非顶层表引用时，缓存的计划被标记为依赖于调用角色
      （Nathan Bossart）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;edcda9bb4">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=57b9d20188f7df33008b88594e942983 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=a64ab1b252fc7fb64f28b8f40db0aa55 sig_cn_org=af11761be56e749c3bbdf78ee5f9871c source=16.8 
     <para>
      If a CTE, subquery, sublink, security invoker view, or coercion
      projection in a query references a table with row-level security
      policies, we neglected to mark the resulting plan as potentially
      dependent on which role is executing it.  This could lead to later
      query executions in the same session using the wrong plan, and then
      returning or hiding rows that should have been hidden or returned
      instead.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      如果查询中的CTE、子查询、子链接、安全调用者视图或强制投影引用了具有行级
      安全策略的表，我们未能将生成的计划标记为可能依赖于执行它的角色。这可能导
      致同一会话中的后续查询执行使用错误的计划，从而返回或隐藏本应隐藏或返回的
      行。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=a64ab1b252fc7fb64f28b8f40db0aa55 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=ab3a30581c8ed2399e290f6f77bf8ee5 sig_cn_org=14acc0a106b7395e775c8748a879291a source=16.8 
     <para>
      The <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> Project thanks
      Wolfgang Walther for reporting this problem.
      (CVE-2024-10976)
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      <productname>PostgreSQL</productname>项目感谢
      Wolfgang Walther 报告了此问题。
      （CVE-2024-10976）
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=ab3a30581c8ed2399e290f6f77bf8ee5 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Michael Paquier <michael@paquier.xyz>
Branch: master [bf8835ea9] 2024-11-11 10:19:52 +0900
