<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=8a90635925042260c8957d7ee9cbd6fc sig_cn_org=bdbbcb14824f7eabc0cdee5256ab673f source=17.5 
     <para>
      Update time zone data files to <application>tzdata</application>
      release 2024b (Tom Lane)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;cad65907e">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;6283ff201">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      更新时区数据文件到<application>tzdata</application> 2024b版本（Tom Lane）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;cad65907e">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;6283ff201">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=8a90635925042260c8957d7ee9cbd6fc -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=7969f381afc1b2e1669a1c2de8be1905 sig_cn_org=b29c772b4e6a5bc6648651b5fd19c4f4 source=16.8 
     <para>
      This <application>tzdata</application> release changes the old
      System-V-compatibility zone names to duplicate the corresponding
      geographic zones; for example <literal>PST8PDT</literal> is now an
      alias for <literal>America/Los_Angeles</literal>.  The main visible
      consequence is that for timestamps before the introduction of
      standardized time zones, the zone is considered to represent local
      mean solar time for the named location.  For example,
      in <literal>PST8PDT</literal>, <type>timestamptz</type> input such
      as <literal>1801-01-01 00:00</literal> would previously have been
      rendered as <literal>1801-01-01 00:00:00-08</literal>, but now it is
      rendered as <literal>1801-01-01 00:00:00-07:52:58</literal>.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      此次<application>tzdata</application>版本更新将旧的System-V兼容时区名称更改为
      对应地理时区的副本；例如<literal>PST8PDT</literal>现在是
      <literal>America/Los_Angeles</literal>的别名。主要的可见后果是，
      对于标准化时区引入之前的时间戳，该时区被认为代表命名位置的当地
      平均太阳时间。例如，在<literal>PST8PDT</literal>中，
      <type>timestamptz</type>输入如<literal>1801-01-01 00:00</literal>之前
      会被渲染为<literal>1801-01-01 00:00:00-08</literal>，但现在
      渲染为<literal>1801-01-01 00:00:00-07:52:58</literal>。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=7969f381afc1b2e1669a1c2de8be1905 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=dacff18931de95ca4ae06d37f045a484 sig_cn_org=3a6b8591603412338c7ad31a8fa36baf source=16.8 
     <para>
      Also, historical corrections for Mexico, Mongolia, and Portugal.
      Notably, <literal>Asia/Choibalsan</literal> is now an alias
      for <literal>Asia/Ulaanbaatar</literal> rather than being a separate
      zone, mainly because the differences between those zones were found to
      be based on untrustworthy data.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      此外，对墨西哥、蒙古和葡萄牙进行了历史修正。
      值得注意的是，<literal>Asia/Choibalsan</literal>现在是
      <literal>Asia/Ulaanbaatar</literal>的别名，而不是一个单独的
      时区，主要是因为发现这些时区之间的差异基于不可靠的数据。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=dacff18931de95ca4ae06d37f045a484 -->
    </listitem>

   </itemizedlist>

  </sect2>
 </sect1>

 <sect1 id="release-17">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=90c9e7fd501b0c8bdcee7e841435c047 sig_cn_org=485657b377c952d44bfe2dad13c30bca source=17.5 
  <title>Release 17</title>
________________________________________________________-->
  <title>发布 17</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=90c9e7fd501b0c8bdcee7e841435c047 -->

  <formalpara>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=c45e8127eac45f2347bf1713afaeffda sig_cn_org=253305b4c6dff5b87ef36e3c2d95e52e source=15.7 
   <title>Release date:</title>
________________________________________________________-->
   <title>发布日期：</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=c45e8127eac45f2347bf1713afaeffda -->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=89a892a0996f862c077f5d88247372a9 sig_cn_org=89a892a0996f862c077f5d88247372a9 source=17.5 
   <para>2024-09-26</para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>2024-09-26</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=89a892a0996f862c077f5d88247372a9 -->
  </formalpara>

  <sect2 id="release-17-highlights">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=13508788fd8dee2d1f9c928870e99338 sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
   <title>Overview</title>
________________________________________________________-->
   <title>概述</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=13508788fd8dee2d1f9c928870e99338 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=386274a8bb01686a2672ba19fbbda050 sig_cn_org=cb5a97aab14ffbffcf489f29f4bfdaab source=17.5 
   <para>
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 17 contains many new features
    and enhancements, including:
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 17 包含许多新功能和增强特性，具体包括：
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=386274a8bb01686a2672ba19fbbda050 -->

   <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=9f391425f3ee326f1ab88c3fad2c31c8 sig_cn_org=56b0a6139fe1dfcb5363ed258dc36044 source=17.5 
     <para>
      New memory management system for <command>VACUUM</command>, which reduces
      memory consumption and can improve overall vacuuming performance.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      新的内存管理系统用于<command>VACUUM</command>，它减少了内存消耗并能提升整体
      的清理性能。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=9f391425f3ee326f1ab88c3fad2c31c8 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=54bad81f14f1eafc25e67d280d1f361c sig_cn_org=d4a222167c2e9cf86d44263c8335cb6b source=17.5 
     <para>
      New <acronym>SQL/JSON</acronym> capabilities, including constructors,
      identity functions, and the <link
      linkend="functions-sqljson-table"><function>JSON_TABLE()</function></link>
      function, which converts JSON data into a table representation.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      新的<acronym>SQL/JSON</acronym>功能，包括构造函数、标识函数，以及
      <link linkend="functions-sqljson-table"><function>JSON_TABLE()</function></link>
      函数，该函数将JSON数据转换为表格表示形式。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=54bad81f14f1eafc25e67d280d1f361c -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=45f0b342c528d7816c435b923e8b89e6 sig_cn_org=3a5cc0ad92c318bf54437fb58ced4db7 source=17.5 
     <para>
      Various query performance improvements, including for sequential reads
      using streaming I/O, write throughput under high concurrency, and
      searches over multiple values in a <link linkend="btree">btree</link>
      index.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      各种查询性能改进，包括使用流式I/O的顺序读取、高并发下的写入吞吐量，以及
      对<link linkend="btree">btree</link>索引中多个值的搜索。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=45f0b342c528d7816c435b923e8b89e6 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=090ac1c7e61c44a56e01b56bf070374e sig_cn_org=15f5ad4c03b9fd50d3cfef5870089b55 source=17.5 
     <para>
      Logical replication enhancements, including:
      <itemizedlist>
       <listitem>
        <para>
         Failover control
        </para>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
        <para>
         <link
          linkend="app-pgcreatesubscriber"><application>pg_createsubscriber</application></link>,
          a utility that creates logical replicas from physical standbys
        </para>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
        <para>
         <link
          linkend="pgupgrade"><application>pg_upgrade</application></link> now
          preserves logical replication slots on publishers and full
          subscription state on subscribers.  This will allow upgrades
          to future major versions to continue logical replication without
          requiring copy to resynchronize.
        </para>
       </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      逻辑复制增强功能，包括：
      <itemizedlist>
       <listitem>
        <para>
         故障转移控制
        </para>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
        <para>
         <link
          linkend="app-pgcreatesubscriber"><application>pg_createsubscriber</application></link>，
          一个用于从物理备用创建逻辑副本的工具
        </para>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
        <para>
         <link
          linkend="pgupgrade"><application>pg_upgrade</application></link> 现在
          保留发布者上的逻辑复制槽和订阅者上的完整订阅状态。
          这将允许升级到未来的主要版本时继续逻辑复制，
          无需复制以重新同步。
        </para>
       </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=090ac1c7e61c44a56e01b56bf070374e -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=70d70e90ebd3ed595aa17ce32e84c92a sig_cn_org=82ae53c8720954d29ea9d01936ac431f source=17.5 
     <para>
      New client-side connection option, <link
      linkend="libpq-connect-sslnegotiation"><literal>sslnegotiation=direct</literal></link>,
      that performs a direct TLS handshake to avoid a round-trip negotiation.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      新的客户端连接选项，<link
      linkend="libpq-connect-sslnegotiation"><literal>sslnegotiation=direct</literal></link>，
      该选项执行直接的 TLS 握手以避免往返协商。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=70d70e90ebd3ed595aa17ce32e84c92a -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=e4f6c5ec74ac2a60c887755328197dc2 sig_cn_org=8ef3522483dbac4ca2f63572595ce8b6 source=17.5 
     <para>
      <link
       linkend="app-pgbasebackup"><application>pg_basebackup</application></link>
      now supports incremental backup.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      <link
       linkend="app-pgbasebackup"><application>pg_basebackup</application></link>
      现在支持增量备份。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=e4f6c5ec74ac2a60c887755328197dc2 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=b2ae46050942196ab707e3e56bb2bf2d sig_cn_org=b15845c4bd10ec1fb927203eb581fd1c source=17.5 
     <para>
      <link linkend="sql-copy"><command>COPY</command></link> adds a new option,
      <literal>ON_ERROR ignore</literal>, that allows a copy operation to
      continue in the event of an error.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      <link linkend="sql-copy"><command>COPY</command></link> 添加了一个新选项，
      <literal>ON_ERROR ignore</literal>，允许在发生错误时继续执行复制操作。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=b2ae46050942196ab707e3e56bb2bf2d -->
    </listitem>
   </itemizedlist>

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=ae622335d4a4b04736cf3165703d382f sig_cn_org=3175cea8b05f97e3ef457a0ef0ca3a52 source=17.5 
   <para>
    The above items and other new features of
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 17 are explained in more detail
    in the sections below.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    上述项目和其他<productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 17的新功能将在下面的章节中
    进行更详细的说明。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=ae622335d4a4b04736cf3165703d382f -->

  </sect2>

  <sect2  id="release-17-migration">

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=400a90eb79f41a38280314085578a73d sig_cn_org=2bbc2b11b6841eda57eb7d1b7f131632 source=17.5 
   <title>Migration to Version 17</title>
________________________________________________________-->
   <title>迁移到版本17</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=400a90eb79f41a38280314085578a73d -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=5b9f61db6c635ea82b92aa17abd61182 sig_cn_org=186150cca28661dd1b0ab789cfdf3f47 source=16.8 
   <para>
    A dump/restore using <xref linkend="app-pg-dumpall"/> or use of
    <xref linkend="pgupgrade"/> or logical replication is required for
    those wishing to migrate data from any previous release.  See <xref
    linkend="upgrading"/> for general information on migrating to new
    major releases.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    需要使用<xref linkend="app-pg-dumpall"/>进行转储/恢复，或者使用
    <xref linkend="pgupgrade"/>或逻辑复制来迁移数据，以从任何先前版本迁移。
    有关迁移到新主要版本的一般信息，请参阅<xref linkend="upgrading"/>。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=5b9f61db6c635ea82b92aa17abd61182 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=850d669b4de806ebaefdd844363493e9 sig_cn_org=5ff39f3555feccfe736fdfd9a0d5c89c source=17.5 
   <para>
    Version 17 contains a number of changes that may affect compatibility
    with previous releases.  Observe the following incompatibilities:
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    版本17包含许多可能影响与之前版本兼容性的更改。请注意以下不兼容之处：
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=850d669b4de806ebaefdd844363493e9 -->

   <itemizedlist>

<!--
Author: Jeff Davis <jdavis@postgresql.org>
2024-03-04 [2af07e2f7] Fix search_path to a safe value during maintenance opera
Author: Jeff Davis <jdavis@postgresql.org>
2024-07-16 [b4da732fd64] When creating materialized views, use REFRESH to load data.
-->

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=3943233574a3a25a4094c17dfdecacae sig_cn_org=bf62109e26798a03e4940b7bad5314d3 source=17.5 
     <para>
     Change functions to use a safe <xref linkend="guc-search-path"/>
     during maintenance operations (Jeff Davis)
     <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;2af07e2f7">&sect;</ulink>
     <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;b4da732fd64">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
     更改函数以在维护操作期间使用安全的 <xref linkend="guc-search-path"/>
     （Jeff Davis）
     <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;2af07e2f7">&sect;</ulink>
     <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;b4da732fd64">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=3943233574a3a25a4094c17dfdecacae -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=40920edec3d96ae321ff3fe42520cf16 sig_cn_org=9a0da50f7744cfd04e1a0b646c2d1fef source=17.5 
     <para>
     This prevents maintenance operations (<command>ANALYZE</command>,
     <command>CLUSTER</command>, <command>CREATE
     INDEX</command>, <command>CREATE
     MATERIALIZED VIEW</command>, <command>REFRESH
     MATERIALIZED VIEW</command>, <command>REINDEX</command>,
     or <command>VACUUM</command>) from performing unsafe access.
     Functions used by expression indexes and materialized views that
     need to reference non-default schemas must specify a search path
     during function creation.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
     这可以防止维护操作（<command>ANALYZE</command>、<command>CLUSTER</command>、
     <command>CREATE INDEX</command>、<command>CREATE MATERIALIZED VIEW</command>、
     <command>REFRESH MATERIALIZED VIEW</command>、<command>REINDEX</command>或
     <command>VACUUM</command>）执行不安全的访问。表达式索引和物化视图使用的函数，
     如果需要引用非默认模式，必须在创建函数时指定搜索路径。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=40920edec3d96ae321ff3fe42520cf16 -->
    </listitem>

<!--
Author: Michael Paquier <michael@paquier.xyz>
2023-08-28 [165d581f1] Tighten handling of "ago" in interval values
Author: Michael Paquier <michael@paquier.xyz>
2023-08-28 [617f9b7d4] Tighten unit parsing in internal values
-->

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=d6188131e0871624f4dc4c0df4f995ea sig_cn_org=d1984af80d1191f1cc58d4b1f5bba3ac source=17.5 
     <para>
     Restrict <literal>ago</literal> to only appear at the end in
     <type>interval</type> values (Joseph Koshakow)
     <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;165d581f1">&sect;</ulink>
     <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;617f9b7d4">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
     限制 <literal>ago</literal> 仅出现在 <type>interval</type> 值的末尾（Joseph Koshakow）
     <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;165d581f1">&sect;</ulink>
     <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;617f9b7d4">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=d6188131e0871624f4dc4c0df4f995ea -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=95383c8c5d60426414d4280cc5daf65d sig_cn_org=0e3ed32acc4a4a43ea5c33536af7347b source=17.5 
     <para>
     Also, prevent empty interval units from appearing multiple times.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
     同时，防止空的区间单位多次出现。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=95383c8c5d60426414d4280cc5daf65d -->
    </listitem>

<!--
Author: Thomas Munro <tmunro@postgresql.org>
2023-09-05 [f691f5b80] Remove the "snapshot too old" feature.
-->

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=00425ed877a2f800a8d9bf6d5560c4e1 sig_cn_org=e8df5df35c40d282d64acb62475e1afe source=17.5 
     <para>
     Remove server variable old_snapshot_threshold (Thomas Munro)
     <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;f691f5b80">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
     移除服务器变量 old_snapshot_threshold（Thomas Munro）
     <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;f691f5b80">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=00425ed877a2f800a8d9bf6d5560c4e1 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=d147900d59d822888a82c6d6a78c4678 sig_cn_org=4828b031cba0cb955f8702f589a30358 source=17.5 
     <para>
     This variable allowed vacuum to remove rows that potentially could
     be still visible to running transactions, causing "snapshot too
     old" errors later if accessed.  This feature might be re-added
     to <application>PostgreSQL</application> later if an improved
     implementation is found.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
     该变量允许 vacuum 删除那些可能仍对正在运行的事务可见的行，
     否则如果访问这些行，后续会导致“快照过旧”错误。该功能可能会在
     发现更好的实现后重新添加到 <application>PostgreSQL</application> 中。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=d147900d59d822888a82c6d6a78c4678 -->
    </listitem>

<!--
Author: Nathan Bossart <nathan@postgresql.org>
2023-07-13 [a0363ab7a] Fix privilege check for SET SESSION AUTHORIZATION.
-->

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=1537b86e8a0d353518ba9a111d1e984d sig_cn_org=ff7bfe96b5941602a110c85b6f5d68cb source=17.5 
     <para>
     Change <link linkend="sql-set-session-authorization"><command>SET
     SESSION AUTHORIZATION</command></link> handling of the initial
     session user's superuser status (Joseph Koshakow)
     <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;a0363ab7a">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
     更改<link linkend="sql-set-session-authorization"><command>SET
     SESSION AUTHORIZATION</command></link>对初始会话用户超级用户状态的处理（Joseph Koshakow）
     <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;a0363ab7a">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=1537b86e8a0d353518ba9a111d1e984d -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=9977b33b8a572a7d9065314559ef9b7c sig_cn_org=5db732b67f01553c739762ec49f2c003 source=17.5 
     <para>
     The new behavior is based on the session user's superuser status at
     the time the <command>SET SESSION AUTHORIZATION</command> command
     is issued, rather than their superuser status at connection time.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
     新行为基于会话用户在执行<command>SET SESSION AUTHORIZATION</command>命令时的超级用户状态，
     而不是他们连接时的超级用户状态。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=9977b33b8a572a7d9065314559ef9b7c -->
    </listitem>

